Articles.Content:
Looking at this section here:

Error occurred at 2015-06-30_191832.
F:\Jogo\SteamLibrary\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program\KSP.exe, run by antonywilliam.
95% memory in use.
2986 MB physical memory [133 MB free].
0 MB paging file [2248 MB free].
2048 MB user address space [149 MB free].
Write to location 00400000 caused an access violation.

It seems that you only have 3GB of RAM in your computer, and KSP is crashing because it needs much more RAM than is available - you may need to consider buying higher-capacity RAM sticks, or even upgrade to a better computer altogether.

Also, I've taken the liberty of putting your log file output between 

 tags, to make it easier to read your posts.

Running the game on 3GB is doable, but you are going to have to shut down all non-essential services. Open the task manager to see what all is running on startup, then google each process to find out what you can shut down and what you can't.

Memory upgrades are relatively inexpensive, but can be a MAJOR pain, especially on older motherboards, mainly because it can be difficult to find compatible memory sticks, and/or the necessity to update/flash the bios.

Active Texture Management may be worth a try : http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/59005-1-0-Release-5-0-April-28-2015-Active-Texture-Management-Save-RAM!, but I personally haven't tried it yet with any of the 1.0.x releases, and there are some reports that it doesn't help that much anymore. But with only 3GB, every little bit could make a difference.

It also looks very much like you are running a 32 bit version of windows which restricts the amount of memory KSP can use to 2 gig. You should either try the -forceopengl option or reduce the texture quality in the settings by one or two notches. Both of these should reduce the amount of ram it will need though, given the various memory leaks, you still probably won't be able to run for very long before crashing.
